                            <comment id="14476736" author="pschumacher" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2014 04:16:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I created a &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/groovy/groovy-core/pull/529&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;pull request&lt;/a&gt; with a simple solution. Discussion welcome (as usual). &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14476671" author="jkemnade" created="Fri, 31 Oct 2014 04:27:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This should definitely fix the leak. However, if you&apos;re worried about performance, you could as well use a regular (not subclassed) &lt;tt&gt;ThreadLocal&lt;/tt&gt; and set its value lazily in the &lt;tt&gt;writeDate&lt;/tt&gt; method.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; void writeDate(Date date, CharBuf buffer) {
  SimpleDateFormat formatter = dateFormatter.get();
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (formatter == &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;null&lt;/span&gt;){
    formatter = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; SimpleDateFormat(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;yyyy-MM-dd&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;T&apos;&lt;/span&gt;HH:mm:ssZ&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, Locale.US);
    formatter.setTimeZone(TimeZone.getTimeZone(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;GMT&quot;&lt;/span&gt;));
    dateFormatter.set(formatter);
  }
  buffer.addQuoted(formatter.format(date));
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14476593" author="pschumacher" created="Thu, 6 Nov 2014 12:06:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Merged the pull request. Thanks for reporting this issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
